[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged after dash cam overtaking investigation

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 47-year-old man has been charged with dangerous driving after dash cam footage of a road incident in Moray was posted on social media.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police Scotland said they had been alerted to footage showing a car overtaking on the A941 Lossiemouth to Elgin road.
The incident allegedly occurred on Tuesday 8 March.
Police said irresponsible drivers should be aware dash cams were now in common use in all types of vehicles.
